    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>July 20.'59</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Mr. I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">From the <sic>Inclosed</sic><lb/> you will perceive that I am
                still<lb/> provided with pens, paper &amp; ink.<lb/> Publish the article <hi
                    rend="underline">unabridged</hi>,<lb/> or not at all. I can assure you<lb/> that
                the heat is so excessive that it<lb/> almost unfits me for even the<lb/> slightest
                mental labor. I never<lb/> suffered so much from Southern<lb/> heat as this
                summer.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please <hi rend="underline">read</hi> the <sic>Inclosed</sic>
                letter<lb/> &amp; then hand it to <persName>Mr. M.</persName> I can<lb/> tell you he
                has no superior-<lb/> if his equal—in Talmudical</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Scholarship in this country.<lb/> He has two great faults, of which<lb/> I often
                reproached him: he<lb/> never writes anything,—and<lb/> leads too retired a life.
                I<lb/> hope <placeName>America</placeName> will <hi rend="underline"
                >reform</hi><lb/> him in these two things, if<lb/> in nothing else.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">More anon—<add>?</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(3 )">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">M Mayer</persName>
            </p>
